This means that the non-open procedure is now very similar to the open procedure.
In Germany, the contracting entities have largely followed the guidelines on the priority of the open procedure or the public invitation to tender. In the Czech Republic, some services have been allocated inadmissibly in order to avoid the requirements for the choice of the type of contract.
Taking into account the EU threshold, errors had to be found in Germany, which resulted in a fall below the minimum share of services offered throughout the EU.
In the Czech Republic, there is still no satisfactory solution to accurately determine the expected cost of works and construction projects.
