Prior information and notice
In the case of construction projects with construction services to be awarded throughout Europe, the public client must inform interested companies about the planned Awards in advance of the invitation to tender.
Preliminary information and notices form an important basis for pan-European competition.
Requirements of EU law and the Prevention of corruption
The preliminary information shall contain the essential information relating to the construction projects envisaged under public procurement law.
They are necessary for those construction projects where the total estimated value of the contract reaches or exceeds the EU threshold and where the contracting entity intends to reduce the time-limits for open or restricted procedures.
In notices, the contracting authority shall specify binding details of the works contracts to be awarded throughout Europe.
