Conclusion of the procurement procedure
After examination and evaluation of the tenders, the award procedure shall be completed by the award of the contract or by the repeal of the procedure.
Requirements of EU law and the Prevention of corruption
In the case of EU-wide procurement procedures, all tenderers must be informed in advance of the proposed procurement decision.
Companies have the option of examining the intended award in the event of information by electronic means or by fax within 10 days or in the case of other means of communication within 15 days and, where appropriate, to initiate a review procedure.
A contract may not be concluded before the end of this period of information.
