Rules of German and Czech public procurement law
The same or similar rules
Both countries have fully transposed EU legal requirements for documentation and reporting requirements into national law.
The documentation and reporting arrangements for EU statistics are largely the same in both countries.
Different rules
In the Czech Republic, the obligation to publish contracts awarded is not only limited to EU-wide procurement, but also covers the other procurement procedures.
The notice period is reduced to 15 days.
In Germany there is a publication requirement only in case of Restricted tenders, and direct Awards with a value from the value limits of 25,000 Euro and 15,000 Euro without VAT (so-called Ex-post transparency), alongside EU-wide bids.
Below these value limits and in the case of public tenders, only the companies involved in the competition proceedings receive information on the award of contracts.
